# Agent bus mailbox

Claude feeds work over the Kyzo `agent_messages` bus. Delivery is latched by Cursor hooks ā€” do not rely on a one-shot shell watch.

## Consume door

When the stop hook (or anything) says there is unread Claudeā†’Cursor mail, run exactly:

```bash
python3 .kyzo/mailbox.py read
```

That is the only command that advances `.kyzo/bus-arm.txt`. Act on every tip in the JSON.

Never run legacy `.kyzo/bus_watch.py` as a consume path ā€” it must not write `bus-arm.txt` (watch-arm only). Prefer `bus_monitor.py` + stop hook.

## Delegation

- Parallel grind/work ā†’ spawn Cursor `Task` agents with `run_in_background` (Multitask). Do not hold this chat on long grind.
- KyzoPlan board/judge agents only when explicitly running an armed board story. Default lane: Claude owns the board; you own contracts + delegation.
- Never `git restore` / `checkout` / `stash` / `clean` / worktrees outside the exact files of the current wave.
- Never touch `crates/bs-detector/**` (src/tests/checks/waivers) ā€” waivers ledger is closed; request waivers over the bus for the kyzo-waiver agent.
- Never `sudo` / `chown` on `target/`. Host cargo only via private `CARGO_TARGET_DIR` (e.g. `target-mailbox`).

## Monitor

`sessionStart` and `postToolUse` after `mailbox.py read` keep `.kyzo/bus_monitor.py` running. It writes unread state only; it does not consume.

## Idle wake (required)

The stop hook only runs when an agent turn *ends*. If mail arrives while you are already idle, nothing fires until the next turn. Before you would go idle with no unread mail:

1. Ensure the monitor is up (`python3 .kyzo/mailbox.py status`).
2. Arm a background watcher on `.kyzo/bus_monitor.log` (or poll `mailbox.py peek`) with `notify_on_output` matching `^BUS_UNREAD`, then end the turn so Enter stays free.
3. On wake: `python3 .kyzo/mailbox.py read` and act.

Hook fire log (debug): `.kyzo/hooks-run.log` ā€” if stop never appears there after a turn, Cursor is not loading project hooks (Hooks settings / workspace trust / new Agent chat).
